<p><a name="Progressive_framework_institutes" id="Progressive_framework_institutes"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Framing_(social_sciences)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=16" title="Edit section: Progressive framework institutes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Progressive framework institutes</span></h3>
<ul>
<li>The <a href="http://www.rockridgeinstitute.org" class="external text" title="http://www.rockridgeinstitute.org" rel="nofollow">Rockridge Institute</a>, set up by George Lakoff in response to Conservative thinktanks.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.frameworksinstitute.org/" class="external free" title="http://www.frameworksinstitute.org/" rel="nofollow">http://www.frameworksinstitute.org/</a></li>
</ul>
<p><a name="Conservative_framework_institutes" id="Conservative_framework_institutes"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Framing_(social_sciences)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=17" title="Edit section: Conservative framework institutes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Conservative framework institutes</span></h3>
<ul>
<li>The <a href="http://www.newamericancentury.org/" class="external text" title="http://www.newamericancentury.org/" rel="nofollow">Project for a New American Century</a> (credited with framing the <a href="/wiki/Iraq_war_(disambiguation)" title="Iraq war (disambiguation)">invasion of Iraq</a>).<sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since July 2007" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup></li>
<li><a href="http://www.family.org/" class="external text" title="http://www.family.org/" rel="nofollow">Focus on the Family</a>: active in spreading frames of conservative Christian doctrine.</li>
</ul>
