<li id="cite_note-23"><b><a href="#cite_ref-23" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=8271086&amp;dopt=Abstract" class="external text" title="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=8271086&amp;dopt=Abstract" rel="nofollow">The framing effect of relative and absolute risk. [J Gen Intern Med. 1993] - PubMed Result</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-24"><b><a href="#cite_ref-24" title="">^</a></b> De Martino, B., Kumaran, D., Seymour, B., and Dolan, R. J. (2006). Frames, biases, and rational decision-making in the human brain. Science 313, 684-687.</li>
</ol>
</div>
<table class="navbox" cellspacing="0" style=";">
